   <text>
      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0531.jpg" n="part4_p057.jpg" xml:id="img_0057" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p057.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_57_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>526.
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>here again, Protestant, or older Catholic tradition; and here again, Puritan or Lutheran
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>traditions; and here again, European Protestantism and America Protestantism—everybody
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>is within the situation that he has to make decisions, because he is NOT one monolithe
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>tradition in which he knows what to do because of the authority of the tradition.
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>This brings us to the question: What is the relationship of the ABSDLUTE
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>VALIDITY of the catogorical imperative, which weiuscussed last time, and the IELATIVE
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>VALIDITY of every content which HAPPENS in the esthical act? How can you act with the
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>feeling of conconditional duty if you are corn in your consciousness about the CONTENTS of
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>this duty? Now this is a very serious practical problem, I believe, and I hope for all of, you
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>who have an ethically hoisitive conscience and at the same time the pathos of autonomy in
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_57_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>your judgment and not the acceptance of traditionalism and conformism. Of course, this is
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>not self-understood. There are different ways of deriving, from the ultimate principle of others,
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>contents which then must be accepted as
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>unconditional themselves. I will
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>refer to two of these: the Catholic doctrine of natural law, and the totalitarian ideas.
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>In the Roman Catholic doctrine of natural law—when by chance I say
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>"Catholic" with the adjektive "Roman," please, [I mean also] the Anglo-Catholis and the Greek
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>Catholics—don’t feel hit, necessarily; it's a European tradition, where, in the practical life,
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>ari, in Germany,
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_3_tl_10" n="N010"/>Catholicism is identified with Roman Catholicism—and it took me
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_57_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>years in this country before I realized that this is misleading because here the word "Catholic" is
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>also used for some Protestant groups.
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>Now the Roman Catholic position is the following—and it is a very realistic one,
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>in our present situation here in America, where we have a powerful representation of a natural¬
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>law theory which ishnaintained and confirmed by the authority of the Church. Let me develop
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>this idea a little bit.
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>Au dʼune
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>de bon augure.
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>cʼest lʼautreur de ses
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>Monsieur Mlle Décembre, ou de lʼhonneur de ses
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>je mʼadresse à nous
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>de mon ami
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>devenu
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>dans cette teinte vieuse
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>Votre très-hier
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>qui me
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_17" n="N017"/>dʼêtre
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_18" n="N018"/>dire une
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_19" n="N019"/>dʼavoir lʼautre beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_20" n="N020"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_21" n="N021"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_57_tr_1_tl_22" n="N022"/>Monsieur Mʼa paru
            </p>
            
